00:43:13.010 --> 00:43:16.850
- Yeah, well it's another
classic example of an anomaly.

00:43:16.850 --> 00:43:18.660
It doesn't fit mainstream
thinking science,

00:43:18.660 --> 00:43:21.020
and that was ignored for a hundred years,

00:43:21.020 --> 00:43:23.560
discovered by Francis
Galton in the 19th Century,

00:43:23.560 --> 00:43:25.690
first cousin of Charles Darwin.

00:43:25.690 --> 00:43:29.310
He noticed that some people
in the general population,

00:43:29.310 --> 00:43:30.350
he thought it was very rare,

00:43:30.350 --> 00:43:31.470
people thought it was one in a thousand,

00:43:31.470 --> 00:43:34.590
one in 10,000, we find
one in 50 people has this,

00:43:34.590 --> 00:43:37.030
have this peculiarity that is
when they look at a number,

00:43:37.030 --> 00:43:38.890
black and white number, black letter,

00:43:38.890 --> 00:43:42.400
black number five or six or
seven printed on a white page,

00:43:42.400 --> 00:43:43.800
they see the number colored.

00:43:44.770 --> 00:43:46.150
There are two kinds of synesthesia,

00:43:46.150 --> 00:43:48.380
called projectors and associators.

00:43:48.380 --> 00:43:50.330
The projectors literally see the color,

00:43:50.330 --> 00:43:51.870
if you go by their description,

00:43:51.870 --> 00:43:54.487
they'll say, "The five
is, I know it's black,

00:43:54.487 --> 00:43:55.868
"but it looks red to me,

00:43:55.868 --> 00:43:57.257
"and it even has a halo of red around it

00:43:57.257 --> 00:43:58.890
"like a neon light."

00:43:58.890 --> 00:44:01.787
Some people say, "I know it's black,

00:44:01.787 --> 00:44:05.580
"but it looks a beautiful
pink color to me."

00:44:05.580 --> 00:44:07.300
So this is a classic
example of an anomaly.

00:44:07.300 --> 00:44:09.130
