00:44:09.130 --> 00:44:10.140
Are they crazy?

00:44:10.140 --> 00:44:11.490
Secondly, who gives a damn,

00:44:12.830 --> 00:44:15.920
who cares whether these
people see numbers as color.

00:44:15.920 --> 00:44:17.240
I can answer both those questions.

00:44:17.240 --> 00:44:20.240
We embarked on this about 10
years ago for the first time.

00:44:20.240 --> 00:44:22.690
First of all we showed they're not crazy,

00:44:22.690 --> 00:44:23.523
they see the colors,

00:44:23.523 --> 00:44:26.140
I'm going to touch on this
in my talk this evening,

00:44:26.140 --> 00:44:27.870
they see the colors perfectly clearly,

00:44:27.870 --> 00:44:29.340
just like you and I do.

00:44:29.340 --> 00:44:31.270
You can show this by various experiments.

00:44:31.270 --> 00:44:33.872
For example, if you have the number five,

00:44:33.872 --> 00:44:38.872
and it's red, and you surround
it by a bunch of twos,

00:44:41.810 --> 00:44:44.680
you have a black five surrounded
by a number of black twos,

00:44:44.680 --> 00:44:46.110
normal people find it really difficult

00:44:46.110 --> 00:44:47.400
to spot the black five

00:44:48.390 --> 00:44:49.820
because it looks very much like the twos,

00:44:49.820 --> 00:44:52.380
made up of the same vertical,
horizontal components,

00:44:52.380 --> 00:44:55.070
so you got a matrix of fives
with a two in the middle.

00:44:55.070 --> 00:44:57.400
You ask them is there a
two in the display or not?

00:44:57.400 --> 00:44:59.230
And they find it very
difficult to answer that,

00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:02.260
or take several seconds,
maybe 20, 30 seconds.

00:45:02.260 --> 00:45:04.417
These people say, "Oh, I see a red two

00:45:04.417 --> 00:45:05.927
"in the middle of green fives,

00:45:05.927 --> 00:45:07.210
"in a forest of green."

00:45:07.210 --> 00:45:08.459
And they do it much more quickly,

00:45:08.459 --> 00:45:11.080
twice the speed of normal people.

00:45:11.080 --> 00:45:12.210
This shows that we're dealing with

00:45:12.210 --> 00:45:14.480
a genuine, authentic phenomenon.

00:45:14.480 --> 00:45:17.950
Jamie Ward in London has
replicated this result.

00:45:17.950 --> 00:45:20.350
This is what got us going initially,

00:45:20.350 --> 00:45:24.543
and then what causes the
phenomenon of synesthesia,

00:45:26.730 --> 00:45:30.060
it turns out that the
brain is of course modular,

00:45:30.060 --> 00:45:31.290
the adult brain,

00:45:31.290 --> 00:45:33.580
but in early infancy and in the fetus,

00:45:33.580 --> 00:45:35.150
almost every part is
connected to every other part,

00:45:35.150 --> 00:45:37.270
there's tremendous
redundancy of connections.

00:45:37.270 --> 00:45:40.630
There are pruning genes
which then prune off

00:45:40.630 --> 00:45:43.010
excess connections
between adjacent modules

00:45:43.010 --> 00:45:44.310
to create the modular architecture

00:45:44.310 --> 00:45:46.150
that characterizes the adult brain,

00:45:46.150 --> 00:45:47.620
so you get for example,

00:45:47.620 --> 00:45:50.380
an area for color in fusiform gyrus

00:45:50.380 --> 00:45:53.500
in the temporal lobes,
little brain section

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:55.010
called the fusiform gyrus,

00:45:55.010 --> 00:45:57.122
an area for color called V4,

00:45:57.122 --> 00:45:59.950
then an area for number right next to it,

00:45:59.950 --> 00:46:01.650
visual appearance of numbers.

00:46:01.650 --> 00:46:04.450
These are normally segregated
in the adult brain,

00:46:04.450 --> 00:46:06.650
but if there's a defect
in the pruning gene,

00:46:06.650 --> 00:46:09.670
they get connected, and there's a mutation

00:46:09.670 --> 00:46:11.570
in the pruning gene,
there's hyperconnectivity

00:46:11.570 --> 00:46:12.837
between adjacent brain regions,

00:46:12.837 --> 00:46:14.690
and if this hyperconnectivity is expressed

00:46:14.690 --> 00:46:17.930
by transcription factors exclusively

00:46:17.930 --> 00:46:19.990
in the fusiform gyrus, which can happen,

00:46:19.990 --> 00:46:21.870
you get number-color synesthesia.

00:46:21.870 --> 00:46:23.820
Every time you see a
black and white number,

00:46:23.820 --> 00:46:24.670
it activates the number area,

00:46:24.670 --> 00:46:28.550
and it cross-activates the
color area in the brain,

00:46:28.550 --> 00:46:29.570
evoking a particular color,

00:46:29.570 --> 00:46:31.630
so five is red, six is
blue, seven is green,

00:46:31.630 --> 00:46:32.760
so we have a solution to the mystery.

00:46:32.760 --> 00:46:34.927
So we did the perceptual experiments,

